I’ve always wanted to do a Spartan! Did my debut with the Super Spartan Monterrey - turned out to be 10 miles and 22 obstacles- 4 of the obstacles I was not able to do yet (monkey bars mainly) but now that I know what I don’t know… I’m about to work on it!!! Not going to lie, it was challenging but also so freaking rewarding. I was asked how long I trained to be able to do this race (because that is what people do!)… fact is, I train everyday not to do Spartans and obstacle courses but to be strong, confident, agile and have endurance! @fitnessgymoakland on a daily baby!!! Also, very cool to have the opportunity to do this with one of my business partners (whom also took videos of the journey and now I can share with y’all). Gracias a Señor Benjamin and his friends, I had a blast. #spartan #obstacles #race #workout #superspartan
It’s all about enjoying the process. #process #focus #growth #learning #connection #intention #dicipline

It was fascinating to attend my 20th year college reunion at @occidentalcollege this weekend. I have to say, having my son with me at every reunion has been special. We’ve always had a great time. 

As I reminiscence the role @occidentalcollege has played in my life, I feel nostalgia about how this very institution continues to SEE ME. For my 10th year reunion Oxy hired me to perform - full Maríachi and all, it was AMAZING! 

For the 15th year reunion Oxy honored me (thanks to those that nominated me @gladdysuribe @chelychela @_claudia323_ @ahernand99, to name a few)  with the Alumni Seal Award for my contributions to my community. 

And so, I continue to show up as a donor and as an alumna. I loved my experience as a student and I am also loving my experience as an alumna. 

Thank you Oxy staff, professors and administrators that make this day possible - being on campus, staying in the dorms, eating at the marketplace filled my heart this weekend. #alumni #occidental #occidentalcollege #oxy #classof2003 #20thyearreunion #barrackobama

So, this happened last week. I won Entrepreneur of the Year! Thank you @latinastylemag for the recognition and Veronica Rocha, MBA for the nomination. 

When I accepted the award, I was invited to give a speech and... to be honest I was not prepared, all the nominees were so deserving that I thought.. what are the chances lol. But hey, there I was, accepting the award, with the mic on hand sharing with all the attendees how important building community, hiring, and doing business with each other is. I shared how much I love my life, simple but with high community impact... because everything I do aligns with my personal mission of creating generational wealth and facilitating upward mobility for black and brown people. 

This recognition has my name BUT it is one that I share with the Chingona Entrepreneurs that were nominated, Veronica who thought of me for this nomination, both my teams at ESO Ventures and madeBOS, Inc., my partners ( Alfredo Mathew III and Ben Wanzo), advisors, coaches, investors, customers, and... most importantly my support system - my family. There is absolutely no way I would be able to do this if it wasn't for my hardworking mom (Martha Pedroza); she stepped in big time to help me with my son who is now a responsible and independent teenager. 

Anyway, my village is strong and I am grateful for all of you that have been there for me. I am savoring the joy I feel. Gracias! 🥹 #entrepreneuroftheyear #latina #latinastyle #madebos #esoventures #focus #business #entrepreneurship

Becoming our best version is a journey. It requires consistent awareness of where we are at, mentally, physically, emotionally and spiritually (an area I still need to work on). In terms of my physical journey, I used to workout Monday through Saturday, required by my body to improve my mental health. Then, I started making changes because I felt like I hit a plateau. So, I started giving my body more rest. Reduced to 4-5 days instead of 6, changed my workout routine to the mornings (used to go consistently at 8pm), started going to bed at 10-11pm (instead of 12-1am) and sleeping an average of 7-8 hours per day. Also, a huge stressor left my life (a legal issue I was fighting since 2019 and finally won!) and so, all of that combined produced results!!!! 

I have to say, the people I surround myself with have had so much to do with my consistent improvement. From my fitness coaches, trainers, colleagues to my business partners, mentors, fam, friends, etc. when y’all point out and notice the change/improvement- I get that 🔥 in my belly to keep going.

Wednesday-Friday of this past week were hard days for me. You know when you get in your feelings. Well, to help with the turmoil I went to get a full body massage and let me tell you…  that simple act impacted my soul. The healing was real… my body asked for gentle care and my heart for more protection - I let myself be, it was scary (because of the vulnerability) but beautiful. I’ll be posting soon about my massage therapist (cause you know I love supporting my local entrepreneurs) but for now, I’ll leave it at this: 

Becoming a high value woman… is no easy task. Working on me is definitely the best investment ever but also, the most challenging.

Embracing Confidence at Every Age: A Message for my Chicas 🌟

Age is not just a number; it’s a testament to our journey, experiences, and the wisdom we’ve gathered along the way. As women, every year brings us more strength, insight, and beauty, both inside and out.

Let’s redefine what aging means for us. It’s not about losing our youth, but about gaining our power. Our confidence doesn’t diminish with time; it grows, rooted in the knowledge of who we are and what we’ve overcome.

We are not just aging; we are evolving, becoming more of who we’re meant to be.

So, to all the incredible women out there, wear your age with pride. Here’s to growing older, wiser, and even more fabulous! 💪💖

#Confidence #mujer #confianzaabsoluta #confianzaabsoluta #iam42
